    {
      "id": "node-1774630604173",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Results\r\n\r\n  alpha[0] long:  MAE=0.000078  max_diff=0.007  n_bars=863  ✅ \r\n  alpha[1] short: MAE=0.000071  max_diff=0.010  n_bars=863  ✅\r\n  \r\n  No fold-boundary spikes on either model. The earlier nan result was because the previous combo.dropna() was too aggressive — the fix adds:                             \r\n  - n_emitted / n_static counts so you can see if the simulation emitted predictions at all                                                                              \r\n  - is_empty guard with a clear warning message when no bars match (e.g. no primary signals in the window)                                                               \r\n  - Descriptive __repr__ that differentiates between \"empty — try different date range\" vs normal results with MAE/max_diff/n_bars          ",
      "x": -665,
