    {
      "id": "node-1774880170104",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# How cusum is applied\r\n\r\nPipeline order (from source): \r\nsignals → BasicProcessor → trades → minimal_return filter → CUSUM filter → weights → label\r\n\r\n## CUSUM mechanics:                                                                                                         \r\nthreshold(t) = vol(t) × cusum_threshold × close(t)    [in price/dollar units]\r\naccumulate D[close] until sum > threshold → fire event, reset \r\n→ trade only survives if its entry_time hits a CUSUM event \r\n\r\n For cusum_threshold=0.05, volatility_timeframe=4h:\r\n - vol ≈ 1% of price → threshold ≈ 1% × 0.05 × price = 0.05% of price                                                      \r\n - At BTC = $64k → threshold ≈ $31                                                                                                                           \r\n  The real finding — CUSUM is nearly inactive at 15min                                                                   \r\n                                                                                                                            \r\n  ┌─────────────────┬───────────────────┬─────────────────┐                                                               \r\n  │                 │       15min       │       1H        │                                                                 \r\n  ├─────────────────┼───────────────────┼─────────────────┤                                                               \r\n  │ vol used        │ 4h vol = 0.99%    │ 1d vol = 2.56%  │                                                                 \r\n  ├─────────────────┼───────────────────┼─────────────────┤                                                               \r\n  │ CUSUM threshold │ $31               │ $86             │                                                                 \r\n  ├─────────────────┼───────────────────┼─────────────────┤\r\n  │ Median bar move │ $81               │ $156            │                                                                 \r\n  ├─────────────────┼───────────────────┼─────────────────┤                                                               \r\n  │ Threshold / bar │ 0.39×             │ 0.55×           │\r\n  ├─────────────────┼───────────────────┼─────────────────┤                                                                 \r\n  │ CUSUM pass rate │ 80%               │ 73%             │\r\n  ├─────────────────┼───────────────────┼─────────────────┤                                                                 \r\n  │ Fires every     │ 1.2 bars (19 min) │ 1.4 bars (1.4h) │                                                               \r\n  └─────────────────┴───────────────────┴─────────────────┘                                                                 \r\n    \r\n  CUSUM fires every 1-2 bars at 15min — the threshold ($31) is smaller than a single typical bar move ($81), so it resets   \r\n  and re-fires constantly. It's barely filtering anything (80% of bars are \"events\").                                     \r\n                                                                                                                            \r\n  Neither timeframe is doing meaningful CUSUM filtering (73–80% pass rates), but 15min is worse. For CUSUM to be a useful   \r\n  filter you'd want ~20–30% pass rate — which would require raising cusum_threshold to roughly 0.3–0.5 at 15min.",
      "x": -394,
      "y": -2622,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 300,
      "nodeLabel": "N4"
    },
